<paragraph id="8B9D36D17F01AB2F15E93504FB96F9BA" blockId="14.[151,1436,1267,1760]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F15E93504FD52FAC5" authority="Steindachner, 1892" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,641,1303,1328]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F15E93504FD52FAC5" bold="true" box="[151,641,1303,1328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F15E93504FE50FADA" bold="true" box="[151,387,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Dasyatis marmorata</emphasis>
(Steindachner, 
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F173E3504FDAAFAC5" box="[576,633,1303,1328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1892.0">1892</number>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was reported firstly in the Gulf of Gabes (south 
<collectingCountry id="F33576417F01AB2F11C13504FAC7FADA" box="[1215,1300,1303,1327]" name="Tunisia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
) by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F10373504FEB8FAA1" author="Maurin" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Maurin, C. &amp; Bonnet, M. (1970) Poissons des cotes nord-ouest africaines (campagnes de la Thalassa) (1962 et 1968) Revue des Travaux de l'Institut scientifique et technique des Peches maritimes, 34, 125 - 170." type="journal article" year="1970">
Maurin and Bonnet (
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F1456352FFEB0FAA1" box="[296,355,1340,1364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1970.0">1970</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F14EC352EFDF0FAA1" box="[402,547,1341,1364]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pastinaca">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F14EC352EFDF0FAA1" box="[402,547,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. pastinaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F1754352EFD09FAA1" box="[554,730,1341,1364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="variety" variety="marmorata">
var. 
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F1722352EFD09FAA1" box="[604,730,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the presence of this taxon in south 
<collectingCountry id="F33576417F01AB2F1108352FFB1AFAA1" box="[1142,1225,1340,1364]" name="Tunisia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
was confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F15E9354CFE32FA82" author="Quignard" box="[151,481,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Capape C. (1971) Liste commentee des selaciens de Tunisie. Bulletin de la Station d'Oceanographie et de Peche de Salammbo, 2 (2), 131 - 141." type="journal article" year="1971">
Quignard and Capapé (
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F14E1354CFE0AFA82" box="[415,473,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and included in the Mediterranean ichthyofauna by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F1149354CFA4BFA82" author="Quignard" box="[1079,1432,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Quignard, J. P. &amp; Tomasini, J. A. (2000) Mediterranean fish biodiversity. Biologia Marina Mediterranea, 7 (3), 1 - 66." type="journal article" year="2000">
Quignard and Tomasini (
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F102C354CFA43FA82" box="[1362,1424,1375,1399]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2000.0">2000</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Later the species was considered as synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F17B73596FCB9FA69" box="[713,874,1412,1436]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F17B73596FCB9FA69" box="[713,874,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recorded under this name in the eastern and central Mediterranean by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F14BC35B4FD26FA4A" author="Golani" box="[450,757,1447,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Golani, D. &amp; Capape, C. (2004) First records of the blue stingray, Dasyatis chrysonota (Smith, 1828) (Chondrichthyes: Dasyatidae), off the coast of Israel. Acta Adriatica, 45, 107 - 112." type="journal article" year="2004">
Golani and Capapè (
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F17CF35B4FD3FFA4A" box="[689,748,1447,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2004.0">2004</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F164F35B4FBEEFA4A" box="[817,1085,1447,1472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="El Kamel, O., Mnasri, N., Ben Souissi, J., Boumaiza, M., Ben Amor, M. M. &amp; Capape, C. (2009) Inventory of elasmobranch species caugth in the Lagoon of Bizerte (North-eastern Tunisia, central Mediterranean). Pan-American Journal of Aquatic Sciences, 4, 383 - 412." type="journal article">
El Kamel 
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F16D435BAFC0DFA35" box="[938,990,1448,1472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F168635B4FBE6FA4A" box="[1016,1077,1447,1471]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, respectively. However, in the upcoming volume dealing with batoid fishes of the Food and Agricolture Organisation Species Identification Field Guide for Fishery Purposes (Séret, in press), 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F17B335E2FCA5F9FD" box="[717,886,1521,1544]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F17B335E2FCA5F9FD" box="[717,886,1521,1544]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a species of West Africa and Mediterranean and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F140A3606FDC7F9D9" box="[372,532,1556,1580]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chrysonota">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F140A3606FDC7F9D9" box="[372,532,1556,1580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. chrysonota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a South African species; nevertheless a genetic study is needed to reaffirm the validity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F146C362AFE61F9A5" box="[274,434,1593,1616]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F146C362AFE61F9A5" box="[274,434,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and redefine the two species (see also 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F161B3624FBEAF9BA" author="Bradai" box="[869,1081,1591,1616]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B. &amp; Enajjar, S. (2010) Elasmobranchs of the Mediterranean and Black Sea: Status, ecology and biology- Bibliographic analysis. General Fisheries Commission for theMediterranean. 151.1.154.86 / GfcmWebSite / GFCM / 35 / GFCM _ XXXV _ 2011 _ Dma. 3. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">
Bradai 
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F16C9362AFC3BF9A5" box="[951,1000,1592,1616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F16823624FBEAF9BA" box="[1020,1081,1591,1615]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D36D17F01AB2F15E93648FB9DF92A" blockId="14.[151,1436,1267,1760]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F15E93648FDF0F981" authority="Capape, 1975" authorityName="Capape" authorityYear="1975" box="[151,547,1627,1652]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tortonesei">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F15E93648FDF0F981" bold="true" box="[151,547,1627,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F15E93648FEA6F981" bold="true" box="[151,373,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Dasyatis tortonesei</emphasis>
Capapé, 
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F14953648FDF0F981" box="[491,547,1627,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is considered dubious by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F1625364FFBF8F981" author="Compagno" box="[859,1067,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Compagno, L. J. V. (1999) Checklist of living elasmobranchs. In: Hamlett, W. C. (Ed.), Sharks, Skates, and Rays. The biology of elasmobranch fishes. The Johns Hopkins University press, Baltimore, Maryland, pp. 471 - 498." type="book chapter" year="1999">
Compagno (
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F1696364FFBF1F981" box="[1000,1058,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and excluded by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F1185364FFA4FF981" author="Serena" box="[1275,1436,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Serena, F. (2005) Field identification guide to sharks and rays of the Mediterranean and Black Sea. FAO Species Identification Guide for Fishery Purposes. FAO, Rome, 97 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Serena (
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F1027364FFA47F981" box="[1369,1428,1628,1652]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from the “Field identification guide to sharks and rays of the Mediterranean and Black Sea”. Morphometric and meristic data along with parasitological studies on individuals collected in the Gulf of Gabes, seem to indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F15E936DAFEFAF915" box="[151,297,1737,1760]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tortonesei">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F15E936DAFEFAF915" box="[151,297,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. tortonesei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D527F01AB2F17B036DAFB99F92A" authority="Bradai et al., 2010" authorityName="Bradai et al." authorityYear="2010" box="[718,1098,1735,1760]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pastinaca">
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F17B036DAFC8FF915" box="[718,860,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">D. pastinaca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B207F01AB2F161536D4FB91F92A" author="Bradai" box="[875,1090,1735,1760]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refString="Bradai, M. N., Saidi, B. &amp; Enajjar, S. (2010) Elasmobranchs of the Mediterranean and Black Sea: Status, ecology and biology- Bibliographic analysis. General Fisheries Commission for theMediterranean. 151.1.154.86 / GfcmWebSite / GFCM / 35 / GFCM _ XXXV _ 2011 _ Dma. 3. pdf" type="journal article" year="2010">
Bradai 
<emphasis id="B956EAC37F01AB2F16C136DAFC23F915" box="[959,1008,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number id="3DEA24F67F01AB2F117B36D4FB91F92A" box="[1029,1090,1735,1759]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
